Previous Conversation Summary: The bug is in the regular expression used to parse ReAct-style actions (`actionRegex`). It uses a non‑greedy quantifier `(.*?)`, which stops at the first closing parenthesis. This truncates arguments that contain `)` inside the string (e.g., shell commands like `echo $(date)` or `echo "hello)world"`). The shell tool then receives an incomplete command and fails, while tools with simpler arguments (like `list_dir`) work fine because their arguments rarely contain `)`.

The fix is to change the pattern to a greedy match `(.*)` so that it captures everything up to the **last** closing parenthesis on the line (the one that actually ends the action). The dot still does not match newlines, so each action remains on a single line.

Here is the corrected `pkg/agent/parser.go`:


